\ oversized dimensions are rejected rather than silently overflowing int
100000 100000 0-matrix
1000000000 1000000000 0-matrix

\ negative dimensions still rejected
-1 3 0-matrix
3 -1 0-matrix

\ a large-but-valid matrix still constructs; dim reports its shape
100 100 0-matrix dim . .

\ ordinary small matrix is unaffected
2 3 0-matrix dim . .

\ size reports the element count (rows * columns) — the matrix analog of array/set size
cr
2 3 0-matrix size . cr                  \ 6
100 100 0-matrix size . cr              \ 10000
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 1 6 matrix size . cr    \ 6   row vector
[ 1 2 3 4 5 6 ] 6 1 matrix size . cr    \ 6   column vector
1 1 0-matrix size . cr                  \ 1   single element
